--- body ---
## Context
The analysis report must grow linearly with the pipeline (one section per
script) and support selective inclusion so that future papers can pull
only the sections they need. Currently the .qmd hardcodes which includes
to pull; adding a new script means editing the .qmd.

## Design
Each analysis script gets one include in _includes/ (already mostly true).
The analysis report .qmd includes all of them. Future paper .qmd files
include only their subset. The Makefile already controls which figures
each document depends on.

The convention:
- One include per analysis script (e.g., _includes/structural-breaks.md
  documents compute_breakpoints.py)
- Each include is self-contained: method, inputs, outputs, results
- The analysis report .qmd is just a table of contents with includes
- A paper .qmd cherry-picks includes and adds interpretive prose

## Actions
1. Audit: every analysis script in scripts/ has a corresponding include
2. Create missing includes for scripts that lack them
3. Ensure each include declares its script, inputs, and outputs
4. Document the convention in .claude/rules/architecture.md
5. Verify the analysis report .qmd is just structure + includes

## Test
Add a hypothetical new analysis script. The only changes needed should
be: the include file and one line in the .qmd.

## Exit criteria
One include per analysis script. Convention documented. Future papers
can compose from the include pool without editing existing includes.
